text: Olutanga is a Philippine island in the Moro Gulf, part of Zamboanga Sibugay Province. It is separated from the Zamboanga Peninsula by a narrow channel and Tantanang Bay. Olutanga, with an area of , is the largest island in the Moro Gulf and the 34th largest island of the Philippines. It has a shoreline length of . The island is subdivided into 3 municipalities (Mabuhay, Talusan, and the namesake Olutanga), and has a total population of 87,078 people. ==See also== * List of islands of the Philippines ==References== ==External links== * Category:Islands of Zamboanga Sibugay
